subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is separated from the other members of the 

atroglaucum

subgroup by a combination of the following characters: disc of male S4 with short and moderately dense hairs (
Fig. 4B
); male S6 with a pair of thin hair tufts (
Fig. 4B
); and the gonostylus of male genitalia nearly rounded on top (
Fig. 9C
).

STERNA. S4 and S6 normal shaped, not modified. S7–S8 (
Fig. 9E
): S7 with long, apically rounded median process, apex exceeding S8; S8 without median process.
